  <h2>What the Service is</h2>
  <p>
    tela is a markdown-native team wiki. The hosted service at
    <code>telawiki.com</code> includes a wiki editor with real-time collaboration,
    an MCP server so AI agents can read and write your wiki, semantic search and
    Ask (Q&A over your pages), Atlas (AI knowledge generation from connected
    sources), deck presentations, WebDAV sync, and space sharing. We may add,
    change, or remove features at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Accounts and eligibility</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You must be able to form a binding agreement to use the Service. If you are under 18, you need a parent or guardian's consent.</li>
    <li>Provide accurate registration information and a valid email address you control. Confirm your email to activate your account.</li>
    <li>You are responsible for all activity under your account and for keeping your credentials and access tokens secure.</li>
    <li>We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms, threaten the Service or its users, or remain inactive for an extended period.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Break the law, infringe others' intellectual property or privacy rights, or store content you have no right to store.</li>
    <li>Upload malware, attempt unauthorized access, probe vulnerabilities, or disrupt the Service or its infrastructure.</li>
    <li>Abuse, overload, or circumvent rate limits, quotas, or access controls.</li>
    <li>Use the Service to store payment-card data, health records, government-ID numbers, or third-party secrets (see the <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a>).</li>
    <li>Misrepresent your identity or an agent's authority to act on your behalf.</li>
    <li>Use the Atlas AI feature to generate content that is deceptive, harmful, or illegal.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your content</h2>
  <p>
    You retain ownership of the content you create. You grant us a limited,
    non-exclusive right to store, process, search, and display it solely to
    operate the Service for you — including indexing it for full-text and semantic
    search, embedding it for retrieval, and serving it to your team and to AI
    agents you authorize. You are responsible for your content and for having the
    rights to post it. You can export your content as plain markdown or delete it
    at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>AI-generated content (Atlas)</h2>
  <p>
    Atlas is tela's knowledge-generation feature: you connect a git repository
    or Jira project, and Atlas runs an automated pipeline to draft documentation
    pages in your wiki. A few things to know:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Atlas-generated pages are labeled with <code>generator=atlas</code> metadata so you can identify them.</li>
    <li>AI-generated content can be incomplete, inaccurate, or outdated. You are responsible for reviewing it before relying on it or sharing it.</li>
    <li>The source content you connect (git commits, Jira issues) is processed by a self-hosted language model on our servers — it is not sent to any third-party AI provider. See the <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a> for details.</li>
    <li>We grant no warranty on the accuracy or fitness of Atlas-generated content.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>AI agents and the MCP server</h2>
  <p>
    When you connect an AI host (such as Claude or ChatGPT) via OAuth or a
    Personal Access Token, it acts on your behalf with your account's
    permissions. You are responsible for the actions you authorize an agent to
    take, including content it creates, edits, or deletes. Connected AI hosts are
    third parties governed by their own terms and privacy policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Plans, billing, and trials</h2>
  <p>
    tela offers a free Personal plan and paid plans with higher limits. New
    accounts start on a 30-day Plus trial — no card required. After the trial
    ends your account moves to the free Personal plan unless you subscribe.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Paid subscriptions are billed through <a href="https://polar.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Polar</a>, our merchant of record. Polar's terms and privacy policy apply to payment processing.</li>
    <li>Subscription fees are charged in advance on a monthly or annual basis as you select at checkout.</li>
    <li>You can cancel at any time. Access to paid features continues until the end of the current billing period; no partial refunds are issued for unused time unless required by applicable law.</li>
    <li>We may change plan pricing with reasonable notice. Continued use after a price change means you accept the new price.</li>
  </ul>
